This Riedel glass series has something missing; there is no stem or base. Riedel 'O' is the innovative take on the wine tumbler, the designs of which are based on the benchmark shapes of the Riedel Vinum. These are the ideal glasses for every day use and for every occasion; they are fun and feel good to hold.

The 'O' series is a lead free machine blown series, and is dishwasher safe. The 'O' Cabernet/Merlot tumbler is ideally suited to showcase the best characteristics of red wines such as Cabernet, Merlot and Bordeaux.

Chimney Rock Tomahawk Vineyard Cabernet Sauvignon 2009
Drink Organic Wine Gift Set
List.Description:
Jump at this chance to be eco-friendly (and sip some seriously great wines) with this quartet from four of our favorite organic winemakers. The "fruitful" partnership between organic grape growing and winemaking is brings out the best in the vines, and best of all, lets you enjoy the very best that nature has to offer.

Wine Gift Set Includes:

  • California: Paul Dolan Vineyards Organic Zinfandel
    A story of opposites attract. Mendocino County Zinfandel is known for its jammy berry quality and Amador County for its spicy Zins. The Paul Dolan Vineyards Zinfandel is the perfect flavor marriage with tastes of boysenberry preserves, black pepper, and orange marmalade.

  • Italy: Prelius Cabernet Sauvignon
    A vivid ruby color with dark purple traces. The nose is complex, displaying aromas of blackberry and blueberry with hints of vanilla oak and cinnamon. On the palate, the wine is well-structured, showing red fruits and smooth, well-integrated tannins, with a long finish..

  • Spain: Vinos Pinol Sa Natura Organic Red
    Aromas of licorice, minerals, underbrush, blueberries, blackberries and plums leap from the glass. This is followed by sweet, ripe, voluminous fruit with excellent density and concentration.

  • Australia: Yalumba Organic Shiraz
    Magenta in color with purple hues, this hiraz is bursting with varietal aromas of plums and violets, sweet fruit with a forest floor finish. This is a fruit driven, medium bodied wine with fine, soft tannins and a savory, persistent finish.

  • Printed Insert that describes the featured wines

    Due to the popularity of this gift, wines or vintages sometimes sell out. Should this happen, we will always substitute with the current vintage and wines with equal or greater value.
